# AhaDiff

Use this Gemini CLI workspace skill when code changes should be turned into
verified, local learning artifacts.

## Commands

- `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD` captures the latest commit.
- `ahadiff learn --staged` captures staged changes before commit.
- `ahadiff quiz <run_id>` reviews generated quiz questions.
- `ahadiff review` opens the due spaced-repetition queue.
- `ahadiff verify <run_id>` rechecks an existing run.
- `ahadiff improve <run_id>` targets weak evidence or low-score areas.
- `ahadiff serve` opens the local WebUI for lessons, claims, review, and runs.

## Workspace Boundaries

- Treat `.ahadiff/` as per-repository local state unless the repository policy
  explicitly says otherwise.
- `review.sqlite` stores review scheduling and card state.
- Run artifacts under `.ahadiff/runs/<run_id>/` are the evidence source for
  lessons, quizzes, claims, and scores.
- `prompts/` defines the prompt templates used by AhaDiff generation.

Prefer verified claims with file-line evidence. Keep provider secrets in
environment variables and avoid committing private audit logs.
